In 2019, FIFA Best’ awards will be presented in Milan on September 23. "I can’t think of a better time to introduce these awards dedicated to women’s football," said FIFA deputy secretary general Zvonimir Boban. The ceremony now features 11 awards, including the best men’s and women’s player of the year trophies, won in 2018 by Croatia’s Luka Modric and Brazilian star Marta respectively. In 2019 Women’s World Cup in France starts on June 7. 

--AFP--